title: Print, "Design for a Knife Handle Showing Faith", 1600–25
medium: Engraving and etching on off-white laid paper
markings: verso: stamped with ovoid topped by a royal crown and showing crossing diagonal lines, as in 1946-13-1.
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Mrs. A. Murray Young
description: Faith is shown in an ovoid, holding a cross and a book; medallion as in 1946-33-1 at top. Ornament as in 1946-33-1.

exhibitions.title: Feeding Desire: Design and the Tools of the Table, 1500-2005
